CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Flash Newspicture Magazine, February 14, 1938, pg. 23, reads: "They are real sweethearts, Louie and Lena, and here the doughty Louis bids adieu to his attractive wife as the motors of the huge Douglas airliner drone farewell..."Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 5, 1938, pg. 13, reads: "...At right, she is shown an [in] an intimate pose with her husband, the socially prominent Louis Jordan Jones."
TitMainTitle: Lena Horne holding Persian lamb coat and TWA ticket, kissing husband Louis Jones, in front of flight information board at Allegheny County airport
